# CPL Feature Workflow

## When to plan first

For new modules, schema changes, auth/security, or multi-file features:

1. Business objective and affected roles (admin / advertiser / publisher)
2. Affected apps (`platform` vs `tracking`) and packages
3. Prisma entities and migrations (`packages/database`)
4. API routes vs server actions
5. UI routes under `apps/platform/src/app/(admin|advertiser|publisher)/`
6. Security: role checks, session, internal service token for cross-app calls
7. Short implementation plan, then code

## When to implement directly

Bug fixes, copy/styling tweaks, single-file changes, and follow-ups to an approved plan — implement without waiting for approval.

## Product context

LeadFlow CPL: advertisers buy leads, publishers generate them, admin operates the platform. See `.cursor/skills/cpl-platform/SKILL.md` and `docs/PRD.md` for module inventory.

## UI standards

Stripe/HubSpot-inspired SaaS: light theme, Inter, primary `#2563EB`. See `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`.
